    <stitle>HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION WITH TRAILING LEAF SPRINGS - HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION COMPONENTS - TORQUE
        RODS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>TORQUE RODS</title>
        <para>Torque rods are used to minimize rear axle windups, caused by drive line torque and load transfer during
            braking and turning. Some torque rods may be equipped with spacer shims which are used for alignment of the
            axle (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300709">Figure 9</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300710">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0300709" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0300709" filename="../figg03/G0300709.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. TYPICAL TORQUE ROD</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                <callout1>2.STRADDLE MOUNT BAR PIN BUSHING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0300710" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0300710" filename="../figg03/G0300710.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.TRANSVERSE ROD FRAME BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2.SADDLE MOUNT END</callout1>
                <callout1>3.TAPERED STUD END</callout1>
                <callout1>4.IMPACT POINT AREA</callout1>
                <callout1>5.TRANSVERSE ROD AXLE BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>6.LOCKNUT/WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>7.TRANSVERSE ROD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
